import { useEffect, useState } from 'react' export function Stake() { const [Stakes, setData] = useState([]) const handleSubmit = async e => { e.preventDefault() const stakeData = { user_id: userId, match_id: matchId, amount: parseFloat(amount), odds: parseFloat(odds), stake_time: new Date().toISOString(), status: status, } } // Fetch users from the backend useEffect(() => { fetch('http://localhost:4000/api/Stake') .then(res => res.json()) .then(data => setData(data)) }, []) return ( <>
{Stakes.map(stake => (

stake id {stake.id}

stake match_id {stake.match_id}

stake amount {stake.amount}

stake Coef {stake.Coef}

stake stake_time {stake.stake_time}

stake status {stake.status}

))}
) }
